# Site chrome (entire website)

- `UbuntuPageShell` renders one site-wide navbar (`Header shell`) on every public page.
- `SitePageChrome` provides one hero pattern per page; it does not render a second navbar.
- Hero chrome uses negative top margin so the pattern continues behind the shell navbar.
- `PageHero` and `BlogDetail` use `SitePageChrome`; development ribbon is hidden.

# Homepage section order

See `HOME_PAGE_LAYOUT` in `homePageSections.js`.
